<|startoftext|>I would like to update this review after being a few times and trying to figure out my drink order. It was unclear as to what they thought I wanted, but eventually I was seated I ordered a vodka drink and they brought me a mimosa (a light yellow color). I thought the drink tasted really good just didn't feel like it was made in-house. It tasted like it was just poured off a bottle. Then after I sat down at my table I got a bill for an empty glass bottle. The glass was only half full so only got 3 stars. \n\nOther than that the restaurant was very nice. I think they need to do a much better job choosing what they serve or do more of a trial and error when it comes to ordering drinks. Either way it's a good place to stop if you're in the area!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>My daughter went to the clinic last Sunday morning and there was no issue at all after a day of strenuous and pain. They were so patient and easy going that she felt very relaxed and happy. In the end, she got a full and huge facial on Friday and was happy with the results. She always gets great facials, but not when the doctor won't give her a placebo by the same facials to begin with! They are much more thorough and thorough in the appointment than I was expecting. She also got no pain for the first time in a long time. I was afraid she was going to need to have chronic pain, but she doesn't even feel any pain so it was so very much better. I also know our dermatologist could use some work and was not around in this area so I know he's great!  Definitely recommend!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Great ambiance, staff was friendly to a fault, delicious food and service! Absolutely beautiful island and has a very comfortable feel, not pretentious like most Chinese places I've been. My girlfriend even said she feels like a kid again after leaving! Definitely worth your time!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Great food. Super friendly staff. My party of 4 (well of all of us haha) had a bit of everything. Chicken nachos, spicy pulled pork, and chicken wings. All three were yummy. The nachos are a bit heavy on the cheese and meat, but it was worth it. It's also super small and still the nicest bar in the city (despite the fact it's on the small side). Also, the small size means that people are still able to grab hold of you if someone spills your drink or if you need a bathroom quickly.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>We decided to stop here right before our show at Cineplex. After we realized we were late there we realized we were at least 15 mins late. The car was still cool, but I was having trouble getting the wipers to work. At least they changed it so I did not get scuffed up by the cars. When they did, I was so happy, I was even able to fix the problem before the film was over. I will definetly come back for the service and the rest of the movie.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>When I was driving by this place while going to work I noticed that they had a lot of duck wings. I was craving some Chinese food that was not on the block even though my local Chinese food places were a few blocks down the road. This place hit the spot. The menu was very small, which I guess is okay if you are driving by. It's a bit expensive to eat, but the food it comes with is fantastic. \n\nIt has a great variety of dishes! I can get just about everything I want. \n\nI've tried the beef duck and the chicken duck. Both were delicious. Beef duck was full of delicious meat and was the best part! The chicken duck was full of the right proportions of meat and noodles. Definitely worth the extra $. Another plus for this place is that it doesn't take Visa or MasterCard. They accept debit and credit cards.<|endoftext|>
